Package: sqlfluffr
Type: Package
Title: Wrapper to the SQL Linter and Formatter 'sqlfluff'
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Brenden", "Smith",
      email = "brendensmithmi@gmail.com",
      role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")
    )
  )
Description: Provides an R interface to the 'Python' 'sqlfluff' SQL linter and
    formatter via the 'reticulate' package. Lint, fix, and parse SQL queries
    with support for multiple dialects. 'Python' and 'sqlfluff' are
    automatically provisioned on first use with user consent. Includes
    special handling for 'glue' SQL syntax with '{var}' placeholders.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends:
    R (>= 4.0)
Imports:
    reticulate
SystemRequirements: Python (>= 3.0), sqlfluff (https://sqlfluff.com)
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    glue,
    rstudioapi
Config/testthat/edition: 3
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
URL: https://github.com/brendensm/sqlfluffr
BugReports: https://github.com/brendensm/sqlfluffr/issues
